x4freetext: text of contributed paper to Symposium on
Cross Sections from 10 to 50 MeV, Brookhaven,
reactions induced by 30 MeV d(Be) break-up
neutrons on FRT wall and structural materials.
30 MeV deuterons on a 1. cm thick Be target.
Effective neutron spectrum from low energy to
30 MeV, peaked near 14 MeV. The spectrum can
be roughly divided into 3 groups. 2 to 8 MeV
. 0.1 g  of high purity (generally enriched isotope),
sandwiched in Al foil (1. x 1. x 0.1 cm ) and
For tritium counting, 10 target metal foils with
aluminium foil in between irradiated for 10 hours.
Activation and identification of rad. prods.
Chem. separation for the soft radiation
. Si(Li) detector used for x-ray spectroscopy.
. Vacuum extraction and gas counting of tritium
.Includes decay, beta and gamma branching ratios,
The same values in Tbl.1 of rep.BNL-NCS-51245,539,1980
